{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772549164,"nonce":"fh8C4fJEm1ETsUbOdwN9keHVbqo=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87vb9if","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/334","origin":"github"},"title":"Multi-vehicle Gazebo Harmonic simulation for Portsmouth Harbor","message":"## Vision\n\nA single launch file in `marine_simulation` — analogous to the existing `simulator_launch.py`\nbut targeting Gazebo Harmonic — that spawns a multi-vehicle fleet in a realistic Portsmouth\nHarbor world. Vehicles start in autonomous hover mode so they hold position until commanded.\n\n### Fleet\n\n| Vehicle | Platform | Description Package | Gazebo Package | Status |\n|---------|----------|-------------------|----------------|--------|\n| BEN | Custom ASV | `ben_description` | `ben_gazebo` | Gazebo-ready |\n| IzzyBoat | EchoBoat 160 | `izzyboat_project11` (basic URDF) | — | Needs Gazebo integration |\n| BizzyBoat | EchoBoat 240 | — | — | New vehicle; scope TBD |\n| DriX 8 | iXblue DriX | — | — | Has `asv_sim` physics config only |\n\n### Incremental milestones\n\nEach milestone is independently useful and can be a separate issue/PR.\n\n1. **Portsmouth Harbor Gazebo world** — generate and launch a Gazebo Harmonic world from\n   chart data (ETOPO + optional S57 ENC overlay)\n   - Tracked by [unh_marine_simulation#21](https://github.com/rolker/unh_marine_simulation/issues/21) / [PR #22](https://github.com/rolker/unh_marine_simulation/pull/22)\n\n2. **Single-vehicle Gazebo launch in `marine_simulation`** — launch BEN in the Portsmouth\n   Harbor world with full autonomy stack (replacing `sydney_regatta` / `asv_sim`-only path)\n   - Integrate `ben_gazebo` with `portsmouth_nh_gazebo` world\n   - Wire up autonomy stack (helm, mission manager, etc.)\n\n3. **Multi-vehicle spawning** — parameterized mechanism to spawn N vehicles into one Gazebo\n   world at specified positions with proper namespace isolation\n   - Follow VRX's multi-vehicle pattern (YAML config → spawn → bridge)\n   - Start positions in the UNH pier / Cod Rock area (~43.073°N, 70.711°W)\n\n4. **Autonomous hover on startup** — vehicles start in autonomous mode with hover active\n   so they hold position without drifting\n   - Use the autonomy stack's existing hover capability\n   - Contrast with real-boat startup (standby mode) — simulation intentionally differs\n     to prevent idle drift\n   - A startup script or launch event can transition vehicles from standby → autonomous → hover\n\n5. **IzzyBoat Gazebo integration** — create `izzyboat_gazebo` following `ben_gazebo` pattern\n   - SDF model, hydrodynamics, thruster plugins, sensor suite, ros_gz bridges\n   - Extend `izzyboat_project11` URDF/description as needed\n\n6. **DriX 8 Gazebo integration** — create description + Gazebo packages\n   - Visual model, sensor definitions, physics plugins\n   - Leverage existing `asv_sim/config/drix.yaml` for dynamics parameters\n\n7. **BizzyBoat support** — new EchoBoat 240 vehicle\n   - Description, Gazebo, and project11 packages\n   - May share infrastructure with IzzyBoat (EchoBoat 160) — scope TBD\n\n8. **`gazebo_simulator_launch.py`** — top-level multi-vehicle launch in `marine_simulation`\n   - Starts Portsmouth Harbor world\n   - Spawns fleet from config (vehicle type, namespace, start pose)\n   - Brings up autonomy stack per vehicle\n   - Triggers autonomous hover for all vehicles\n\n### Dependencies and related work\n\n- [unh_marine_simulation#21](https://github.com/rolker/unh_marine_simulation/issues/21) — S57 world generator (milestone 1)\n- [unh_marine_simulation#22](https://github.com/rolker/unh_marine_simulation/pull/22) — World generator PR (in progress)\n- [unh_marine_simulation#24](https://github.com/rolker/unh_marine_simulation/issues/24) — OpenStreetMap data for piers/buildings (enhances the world)\n- [unh_marine_simulation#20](https://github.com/rolker/unh_marine_simulation/issues/20) — Tidal water level (future enhancement)\n\n### Notes\n\n- Sub-issues will be opened on the appropriate project repos as milestones are scoped\n- BizzyBoat details (sensor suite, shared infrastructure with IzzyBoat) to be determined separately\n- Station-keeping approach uses existing autonomy hover, not Gazebo physics constraints\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}